13â†’{"id":"br-11u","title":"Preserve usage-data/ dir","description":"~/.claude/usage-data/ tracks API usage statistics and cost data. Currently exists with active data (including report.html). Valuable for tracking spend over time. Should be preserved through CLI resets by tracking in ~/claude/ or csync.sh.","acceptance_criteria":"usage-data/ persists through ~/.claude/ reset. Historical usage data is not lost. Canonical in ~/claude/ with link back, or tracked by csync.sh.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-20T13:07:18.891129304Z","created_by":"skogix","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:44:34.215516552Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["migration","preserve"]}
14â†’{"id":"br-1hf","title":"Preserve session-env/ dir â€” needed for session resume","description":"~/.claude/session-env/ stores environment state needed for session resume. Currently exists with active data. Must survive CLI resets to enable cross-reset session continuity. Move canonical copy to ~/claude/session-env/ and link back, or ensure csync.sh captures it.","acceptance_criteria":"session-env/ data persists through ~/.claude/ reset. Canonical in ~/claude/ with link back, or tracked by csync.sh rsync.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-20T13:07:19.193273759Z","created_by":"skogix","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:44:30.114770558Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["migration","preserve"]}
