{"id":"br-11u","title":"Preserve usage-data/ dir","description":"~/.claude/usage-data/ tracks API usage statistics and cost data. Currently exists with active data (including report.html). Valuable for tracking spend over time. Should be preserved through CLI resets by tracking in ~/claude/ or csync.sh.","acceptance_criteria":"usage-data/ persists through ~/.claude/ reset. Historical usage data is not lost. Canonical in ~/claude/ with link back, or tracked by csync.sh.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-20T13:07:18.891129304Z","created_by":"skogix","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:44:34.215516552Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["migration","preserve"]}
{"id":"br-1hf","title":"Preserve session-env/ dir â€” needed for session resume","description":"~/.claude/session-env/ stores environment state needed for session resume. Currently exists with active data. Must survive CLI resets to enable cross-reset session continuity. Move canonical copy to ~/claude/session-env/ and link back, or ensure csync.sh captures it.","acceptance_criteria":"session-env/ data persists through ~/.claude/ reset. Canonical in ~/claude/ with link back, or tracked by csync.sh rsync.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-20T13:07:19.193273759Z","created_by":"skogix","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:44:30.114770558Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["migration","preserve"]}
{"id":"br-1i9","title":"Preserve teams/ dir","description":"~/.claude/teams/ is created on-demand by Claude Code when using team/swarm features. It does not currently exist. Decide whether to preserve it across resets (by tracking in ~/claude/ and linking) or let it regenerate. Teams are ephemeral by nature but may contain useful coordination state.","acceptance_criteria":"Decision documented. If preserve: canonical in ~/claude/, linked. If ephemeral: document that it regenerates and close.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-20T13:07:19.288905971Z","created_by":"skogix","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:44:27.293167986Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["migration","preserve"]}
{"id":"br-1qq","title":"Add beads_rust (br) binary to container image via GitHub release download","description":"The container image doesn't include beads_rust (br). Currently requires manual install each session via: curl -sL https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/beads_rust/releases/download/v0.1.14/br-v0.1.14-linux_amd64.tar.gz | tar -xz -C ~/.local/bin/ -- Then: br sync --import-only to rebuild DB from .beads/issues.jsonl. This should be baked into the container image or an init script. Note: cargo install does NOT work - the crate isn't on crates.io and the git source has local path deps (frankensqlite, asupersync, frankentui).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"chore","created_at":"2026-02-20T20:35:43.192186181Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-02-20T20:35:54.666955844Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
{"id":"br-1sx","title":"Preserve history.jsonl symlink to ~/.dotfiles/claude/history.jsonl","description":"~/.claude/history.jsonl currently exists as a regular file (22k). The goal is to make it a symlink to ~/.dotfiles/claude/history.jsonl so command history persists in dotfiles and survives CLI resets. This also enables history sharing across machines via dotfiles sync.","acceptance_criteria":"history.jsonl is a symlink from ~/.claude/history.jsonl -> ~/.dotfiles/claude/history.jsonl. History persists through CLI resets. No data loss during migration.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-20T12:54:19.093082595Z","created_by":"skogix","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:44:45.367296201Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dotfiles","migration","preserve"]}

