{"id":"br-2d2","title":"sync beads DB on worktree creation via worktrunk hook","description":"Beads sqlite DB is per-worktree and starts empty. When a new worktree is created, br sync --import-only should run automatically to hydrate the DB from the shared JSONL.\n\nImplementation path:\n- worktrunk manages worktrees, config at $HOME/.config/worktrunk/config.toml\n- easiest entry point: wt hook <name> to register a post-create hook\n- hook should run: br sync --import-only in the new worktree directory\n- also consider: br sync --flush-only as a pre-remove hook to not lose in-flight issues","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-20T18:37:02.609731347Z","created_by":"claude","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:44:15.946552188Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["infra","worktree"]}
